Instantiation   [Creating_Object]
-> In C++, object can be created in two ways..;
        a. SMA(static memory allocation)
            Box b1;     // b1 is an object in C++

        b. DMA(synamic memory allocation)
            Box*p = new Box;
                or
            Box*p = new Box();


.        ***INSTANTIATION IN JAVA***         .
-> In JAVA, object can be created ONLY BY DMA.

        Box b1;             // b1 is note an object
        b1=new Box();       // b1 is a reference variable
            or
        Box b1=new Box();   // if b1 is a local variable
                            // then it is blank when not inialized


